ZH: 他的说法只是一面之词，我们还需要听取其他人的意见。
EN: His words are just one side of the story, we need to hear from others as well.

ZH: 这个事情太复杂了，别轻信别人的一面之词。
EN: This matter is too complicated, don't just take someone's word for it.

ZH: 我们不能只听取一个人的一面之词，需要全面了解这个问题。
EN: We cannot just rely on one person's account, we need to have a comprehensive understanding of the issue.

ZH: 他说的只是一面之词，我们还需要考虑其他可能性。
EN: What he said is only one side of the story, we need to consider other possibilities.

ZH: 不要轻信别人的一面之词，要慎重处理这个问题。
EN: Don't blindly believe in someone's biased account, handle this issue carefully.

ZH: 要有自己的判断力，不要被别人的一面之词左右。
EN: Be able to make your own judgement, don't be swayed by someone's biased account.

ZH: 不能仅仅听取一方的一面之词，应该客观地看待事情。
EN: We cannot only listen to one side of the story, we need to objectively view the situation.

ZH: 在听取证词时，必须避免受到一面之词的影响。
EN: When hearing testimonies, one must avoid being influenced by biased accounts.

ZH: 在处理矛盾时，不能仅仅倾向于听取一方的一面之词。
EN: When resolving conflicts, one should not just listen to one side's biased account.

ZH: 他的陈述只是一面之词，我们需要进一步核实真相。
EN: His statement is just one side of the story, we need to further verify the truth.

ZH: 不要被单一的一面之词所迷惑，要掌握更全面的信息。
EN: Don't be fooled by a single biased account, grasp a more comprehensive understanding.

ZH: 当事情发生纠纷时，要慎重听取各方的意见，而不是仅仅听取一面之词。
EN: When disputes arise, be cautious in hearing from all sides, rather than just listening to biased accounts.

ZH: 如果你只听取一方的一面之词，可能会误解整个情况。
EN: If you only listen to one side's biased account, you may misunderstand the entire situation.

ZH: 在听取汇报时，记得不要被一面之词蒙蔽了视野。
EN: When receiving reports, remember not to let biased accounts cloud your judgment.

ZH: 他的陈述只是一面之词，我们还需要查证是否属实。
EN: His statement is just one side of the story, we need to verify if it is true.

ZH: 要慎重处理听取的信息，避免仅仅受到一面之词的影响。
EN: Handle information carefully, avoiding being solely influenced by biased accounts.

ZH: 当询问时，要记得不要只听取一方的一面之词。
EN: When inquiring, remember not to just listen to one side's biased account.

ZH: 不要以为他的说法就是真相，有时候只是一面之词而已。
EN: Don't assume that his words are the truth, sometimes they are just biased accounts.

ZH: 记得要多方核实信息，不要只听取单一的一面之词。
EN: Remember to verify information from multiple sources, don't just listen to a single biased account.

ZH: 要学会辨别信息的真伪，不要轻信不经核实的一面之词。
EN: Learn to discern the authenticity of information, don't blindly believe in unverified biased accounts.
